[[File:Dmitry Ovtsyn.jpg|thumb|140px|A portrait of Dmitry Ovtsyn by N. V. Pinegin]] '''Dmitry Leontiyevich Ovtsyn''' ({{Lang-ru|Дмитрий Леонтьевич Овцын}}) (unknown - after 1757) was a Russian [[hydrographer]] and [[Arctic]] explorer.
In 1734-1738, Ovtsyn led one of the units of the [[Second Kamchatka expedition]] that charted the coastline of the [[Kara Sea]] east of the river [[Ob River|Ob]]. In summer of 1737, his unit made its way from Ob to [[Yenisei]] and made the first hydrographic description of this part of the Siberian coastline. In 1741, Ovtsyn took part in [[Vitus Bering]]'s voyage to the shores of [[United States|America]]. ==Honours== A cape on the [[Taimyr Peninsula]] and a [[strait]] between the islands [[Oleniy]] and [[Sibiryakow Island|Sibiryakov]] bear his name. ==See also== * [[Russian Hydrographic Service]] ==References== *[https://web.archive.org/web/20100107083109/http://www.polarmuseum.ru/bio/polarex/bio_ovc/bio_ovc.htm Ovtsyn's biography] {{ru icon}}
