{{Infobox book | name = Guitar Zero: The New Musician and the Science of Learning | title_orig = | translator = | image = Guitar Zero book cover.png | image_size = | caption = First edition cover | author = [[Gary Marcus]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United Kingdom | language = [[English language|English]] | series = | subject = | genre = Non-fiction | publisher = [[Penguin Books]] | pub_date = 2012-01-19 | english_pub_date = | media_type = Print, e-book | pages = 288 | isbn = 978-0143122784 | preceded_by = Kluge: The Haphazard Construction of the Human Mind (2008) }}
'''''Guitar Zero: The New Musician and the Science of Learning''''' is a 2012 [[popular science]] book by research psychologist [[Gary Marcus]]. It documents the author's process of learning the [[guitar]] while discussing aspects of [[music cognition]] and the role of [[critical periods]] in learning a musical ability. The book was released on January 19, 2012 and published by [[Penguin Books]], and in December 2012 was released as a paperback under the title '''''Guitar Zero: The Science of Becoming Musical at Any Age'''''.{{citation needed|date=October 2014}}
==Reception==
The book reached 24th on the [[New York Times Best Seller]] list for hardcover nonfiction during the week of February 19, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/best-sellers-books/2012-02-19/hardcover-nonfiction/list.html |title=Best Sellers; Hardcover Nonfiction; Feb 19, 2012 |accessdate=2014-04-24 |date=2012-02-19 |publisher=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref> [[Maria Popova]] on Brainpickings.org named the book among "The Best Music Books of 2012."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.brainpickings.org/index.php/2012/12/21/best-music-books-2012/ |title=The Best Music Books of 2012 |author=[[Maria Popova]] |accessdate=2014-04-24 |date=2012-12-21 |publisher=Brain Pickings}}</ref> In a review for ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'', [[Norman Doidge]] wrote ""Guitar Zero" is a refreshing alternation between the nitty-gritty details of learning rock-guitar licks and Mr. Marcus's survey of the relevant scientific literature on learning and the brain."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424052970203711104577200850417760734 |title=Book Review: Guitar Zero |accessdate=2014-04-24 |author=[[Norman Doidge]] |date=2012-02-01 |work=[[The Wall Street Journal]]}}</ref>
