'''Henrik Johan Walbeck''' (1794-1822) was a [[Finnish people|Finnish]] [[geodesist]] and [[astronomer]] studying the size and [[figure of the Earth]] by means of [[grade measurement]].

He was born on 11 October 1793 in Åbo. In 1817 he was made a corresponding member of the [[Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences]]. He committed suicide on 23 October 1822, also in Åbo.<ref>Uppslagsverket Finland, vol. 3, pg. 480</ref>

