The '''Parakanã people''' or '''Parakána people''' are one of the [[Indigenous peoples in Brazil]], speaking a language of the [[Tupi–Guarani languages|Tupi-Guarani]] group. They traditionally occupy land in the region of the [[Pacajá River|Pacajá]] and [[Tocantins River|Tocantins]] rivers, and subsist by hunting and [[slash-and-burn]] agriculture.

